Step 1: Identify the values needed for the calculation.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from the cash flow statement) = –64,099.10  
• Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 1,493,246.99  

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the formula:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)  

Step 3: Substitute the values:  
 = –64,099.10 / 1,493,246.99  
 ≈ –0.04295  

Step 4: Round to two decimal places.  
 ≈ –0.04

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is –0.04.
